                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13010231" author="bterm" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 17:14:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The .keystore and .truststore where added to the trunk at r1024328 and the branch for 0.6.x was cut at r1056441, but the currently released 0.6.0 tar does not contain these files. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bryan where was the 0.6.0 release made from? the 0.6.0 release date was 2011-02-08 and you added the .keystore files on 2010-10-19 so they should have made it in. Dont see this as a big enough issue to warrant a 0.6.1 release since it will be resolved in any future releases due to the .keystore files being in the 0.6.x branch as well as trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010233" author="brucem" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 17:17:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My guess that I didn&apos;t bother to verify is that it might have been something that excluded files with a leading period in the filename from the release artifacts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010331" author="bterm" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 20:01:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Two issues found with the tar process for making builds&lt;br/&gt;
1. The dist-hook was removing and .&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;a-z&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;* files rather than removing the build and repo files. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. files with names + path that where longer than 99 characters where not included in the archive. (issue with older version of autoconf)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;tar: thrift-0.7.0-dev/lib/java/test/org/apache/thrift/transport/TestAutoExpandingBufferWriteTransport.java: file name is too long (max 99); not dumped&lt;br/&gt;
tar: thrift-0.7.0-dev/contrib/debian/debian: Cannot stat: No such file or directory&lt;br/&gt;
tar: Error exit delayed from previous errors&lt;br/&gt;
gtar: thrift-0.7.0-dev/lib/java/test/org/apache/thrift/transport/TestAutoExpandingBufferWriteTransport.java: file name is too long (max 99); not dumped&lt;br/&gt;
gtar: thrift-0.7.0-dev/contrib/debian/debian: Cannot stat: No such file or directory&lt;br/&gt;
gtar: Error exit delayed from previous errors&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;attached patch fixes both issues and will include the .keystores as well as any new .XYZ files not in the excluded build list. Also changes make dist to be able to be include files with names + path &amp;gt; 99 characters.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010411" author="roger.meier" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 20:36:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Jake!&lt;br/&gt;
just committed your patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010458" author="hudson" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 21:27:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Thrift #99 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Thrift/99/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Thrift/99/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1074&quot; title=&quot;.keystore and .truststore are missing from the 0.6.0 distribution&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-1074&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-1074&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; .keystore and .truststore are missing from the 0.6.0 distribution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;new tar format for dist files: tar-ustar POSIX 1003.1-1988&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds .XYZ files not in the excluded build list to the dist tar.gz file&lt;br/&gt;
Patch: Jake Farrell&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13010838" author="bterm" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 18:51:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;0.6.x branch version of this patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
